thread.title: Egyptians begin voting in contest set to hand Sisi second term

title: Egyptians begin voting in contest set to hand Sisi second term
text: March 26, 2018 / 7:11 AM / Updated 14 minutes ago Voting begins in Egypt's election, President Sisi casts vote - state TV Reuters Staff 1 Min Read CAIRO (Reuters) - Voting began in Egyptâ€™s presidential election on Monday, a contest which is expected to give incumbent Abdel Fattah al-Sisi an easy win and a second term as he faces almost no opposition. An Egyptian soldier keeps guard outside a polling station during the presidential election in Cairo, Egypt, March 26, 2018. REUTERS/Amr Abdallah Dalsh Slideshow (7 Images) Polls opened at 9 a.m. local time (0700 GMT) on the first of three days of voting. Sisi cast his vote in Cairo as the polls opened, state TV reported. Reporting by John Davison; Editing by Gareth Jones
